        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>OFFICE OF										
            &#34;THE JEWISH MESSENGER&#44;&#34;		
            645 BROADWAY.<lb/></p>
            <p><emph rend="italics">Established 1857.</emph><lb/>
                REV. S. M. ISAACS &#38; SON&#44; Editors and Proprietors.<lb/></p> 
            <p>New York. Aug 27 1877<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I am sorry to see by this week&#39;s<lb/> <hi rend="underline">Record</hi> that the omission of your address<lb/> in the Messenger of Aug. 17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> is considered<lb/> a slight.  I hope this is <hi rend="underline">only the editor&#39;s</hi><lb/> opinion&#44; as I need not assure you<lb/> that you have the profound respect<lb/> of father &#38; sons in this office.  Had<lb/> I been in town at the funeral I<lb/> would have had your address re&#45;<lb/>ported in short hand.  Our represen&#45;<lb/>tative&#44; being without instructions from<lb/> me&#44; depended on receiving your mss.<lb/> and took no notes&#44; hence the<lb/> brief &#91;&#63;&#93;.  I am sorry you<lb/> did not send the Mss. last<lb/> week&#8212;it would not have been<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>too late&#8212;and I would<lb/> deem it a personal favor<lb/> if you would send now<lb/> either the funeral address<lb/> or your memorial<lb/> sermon for publication<lb/> this week.<lb/></p>
            <p>Awaiting your reply<lb/> &#38; assuring you of my<lb/> regards<lb/></p>
            <p>Truly yrs<lb/>
            I S Isaacs<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
